data.text:
GENERAL Election 2020 results have started to pour in from across the country.

A number of seats have already been filled by Sinn Fein as their candidates continue to top polls nationwide.

You can keep up to date with results as they roll in over at the Irish Sun's liveblog.

SEATS FILLED: 160/160

FINE GAEL - 35

FIANNA FAIL - 38

SINN FEIN - 37

LABOUR - 6

SOLIDARITY-PEOPLE BEFORE PROFIT - 5

GREEN PARTY - 12

SOCIAL DEMOCRATS - 6

INDEPENDENTS - 19

AONTU - 1

OTHERS - 1

Here are each of the 39 Constituencies results - as they roll in.
